<DOC><DOCNO> AP890419-0119 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-19-89 1339EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-US-Salvador     04-19 0197</FIRST><SECOND>AM-US-Salvador,180</SECOND><HEAD>State Department Condemns Slaying of El Salvador Official</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The State Department condemned theassassination of El Salvador's attorney general on Wednesday as a``brutal, despicable killing'' and charged that the act wasdesigned to provoke further violence.   ``We condemn this terrorism,'' said State Department spokeswomanMargaret Tutwiler.   The official, Roberto Garcia Alvarado, was assassinated byunidentified assailants as he drove to his office in the capital ofSan Salvador. A bomb was placed on the roof of Garcia's JeepCherokee when it stopped at a traffic light.   Although Ms. Tutwiler noted no one had claimed responsiblity forthe attack, she said leftist guerrillas battling the U.S.-backedgovernment have ``engaged in many acts of terror in recent months.''   ``This brutal, despicable killing follows by five days thebombing attack upon the home of Vice President-elect (Francisco)Merino,'' Ms. Tutwiler said, adding that bombing injured a child inthe home.   Ms. Tutwiler said such attacks amounted to ``a campaign ofterror against the people and democratic instutitions of ElSalvador.   ``We condemn this terror, as should all civilized peoples andnations. This campaign is clearly designed to provoke a violentreaction,'' she said.</TEXT></DOC>